<HEADLINE>
<P>
BONDS FOR QUAKE COST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "Sadly, Prop. 1A Is Needed," editorial, May 18: 
</P>
<P>
 It is truly sad that the Legislature and governor always want to pay 
present-day expenses with future tax revenues. We paid for the San Francisco 
quake with a temporary tax, why not again? Proposition 1A should be rejected by 
the people as a message to our elected officials to go back and do their job 
right. 
</P>
<P>
 It is time we in California quit robbing our children and grandchildren to pay 
our expenses; the federal government does a completely adequate job of that 
already. 
</P>
<P>
 L. S. MICHELS 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
