<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION V BASEBALL; CALVARY CHAPEL'S ROSTER OF UPSETS INCLUDES BIG BEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel, which already had beaten the top-seeded team in the Southern 
Section Division V baseball playoffs, added the defending champion to its upset 
list. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles scored on an error in the bottom of the 10th inning to beat Big 
Bear, 3-2, Tuesday in a semifinal game at Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel, the third-place team from the Olympic League, advances to play 
Sierra Madre Maranatha in the final at 2 p.m. Saturday at Blair Field in Long 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles upset No. 1-seeded Los Angeles Baptist, 4-0, in the second round, 
then beat Cambria Coast Union, 8-5, in the quarterfinals Friday. Big Bear won 
the Division V title last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel (20-8) got an outstanding pitching performance from senior 
right-hander J.J. Sandkamp (10-2). Sandkamp, who has all four Eagle playoff 
victories, gave up eight hits and two runs, both unearned. He also had nine 
strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Sandkamp) pitched very, very well," Calvary Chapel Coach Joe Walters said. 
"There is no doubt that he's the top pitcher in the division." 
</P>
<P>
 As Sandkamp was dominating Big Bear, Calvary Chapel kept frustrating its fans 
with failed scoring opportunities -- until the 10th. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Blood was hit by a pitch to start the inning. He went to second when Joe 
Jones walked on a full count. Jones fouled off four pitches with the count full 
before taking an off-speed pitch that was inside. 
</P>
<P>
 Alex Okland then came up in an obvious sacrifice situation. He bunted toward 
third base and Big Bear catcher Jack Iafrate came out to get it. 
</P>
<P>
 Iafrate's throw toward first went past second baseman Mike Brisson, who was 
covering first, and into right field, allowing Blood to score the winning run. 
Okland would have beat the throw. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles had chances to score in the eighth and ninth, but failed. Jones 
walked to start the eighth, went to second on a wild pitch and reached third on 
Okland's infield single. 
</P>
<P>
 But Sandkamp struck out and Jones was out when an attempted squeeze failed. 
Chance King struck out to end the inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel had runners on first and second in the ninth with two outs but 
Jerry Quenzler was picked off second to end the threat. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel had a chance to open a big lead in the fourth. They had a run 
in, the bases loaded and one out but failed to score again. 
</P>
<P>
 "I felt like we could have won it about three times," Walters said. "But these 
guys never get down. They just keep coming back." 
</P>
</TEXT>
