<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION I SOFTBALL; TESSMAN HELPS FOOTHILL BEAT LOMPOC IN NINTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CLIFFORD, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foothill's Robin Tessman didn't have much success in her first three at-bats 
in the Knights' 1-0 extra-inning victory over Lompoc in the Southern Section 
Division I semifinal Tuesday at Canyon High. 
</P>
<P>
 But after striking out, grounding out and reaching base on a fielder's choice, 
Tessman helped win the game despite never putting the ball in play. 
</P>
<P>
 With runners on the corners and none out in the ninth, Tessman fouled off the 
first six pitches she saw from Brave starter Kim Wuest. The seventh pitch 
landed in the dirt, bouncing past Lompoc catcher Becky Hunter, allowing 
Michelle Churnock to score the winning run. The Knights advanced to the final 
against Marina (25-2) on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "One more pitch and I was going to die," Tessman said. "All I had to do was 
battle, and I won the battle. (Wuest) broke first." 
</P>
<P>
 The loss was a bitter end to an outstanding game for Wuest (18-2), a senior 
who struck out 15 and didn't give up a hit until the seventh inning. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't think we were going to get a thing against (Wuest)," Foothill Coach 
Joe Gonzalez said. "We couldn't stay off the high pitch. Our speed game helped 
us. 
</P>
<P>
 "Marie (Gieron) pitched one of her better games. Our defense wasn't quite as 
strong as it has been for her." 
</P>
<P>
 Gieron (12-4) gave up only one hit, a two-out single in the second inning, and 
retired 10 in a row at one point. 
</P>
<P>
 Lompoc couldn't capitalize on its two scoring opportunities. Gieron forced two 
straight pop-outs with runners on second and third in the fourth inning, and 
struck out Colleen Mitchell with two on in the seventh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
