<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: EASTERN SIERRA TROUT ANGLERS HAPPILY THROWN FOR THE LOOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 During the Memorial Day weekend, trout fishermen flocked to the Eastern Sierra 
in numbers not seen since opening day, and those who settled in along the June 
Loop apparently had the most success. 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Stevens of Reseda caught an 8-pound cutthroat trout from shore on a 
Panther Martin lure, and Sean Kaziwara of Ridgecrest took a 6-0 rainbow on 
Power Bait. 
</P>
<P>
 At Gull Lake, Mike Borba of Bishop caught a 5-0 rainbow on an olive woolly 
bugger fly. At Grant Lake, Bruce Hill of Downey landed a 4-11 rainbow on a gold 
Hot Shot lure, and at Rush Creek Bill Hansen of Los Alamitos caught a 3-9 
rainbow on red salmon eggs. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've had some excellent fishing, and on a little bit of everything -- not 
just Power Bait," Elayne Logue of Ernies Tackle said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
