<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP PLAYOFFS AT A GLANCE; SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' TEAM TENNIS FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Today's pairings: Division I -- Santa Barbara (24-0) vs. Dana Hills (23-0) at 
Knollwood Tennis Club (Montecito). III -- Pasadena Poly (19-3) vs.Brentwood 
(18-3) at Riviera Country Club. IV -- Santa Ynez (19-3) vs. Calabasas (16-4) at 
Agoura High, all at 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's champions: Division I -- Santa Barbara. III -- Burbank. IV -- 
Nordhoff. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Santa Barbara has won six consecutive team titles. The Dons finished 
the season undefeated despite the loss of Alex Decret, who graduated after last 
season. Decret won the 1993 Southern Section singles championship and gave the 
Dons their only singles victories in their 11-7 victory over Peninsula in last 
season's team final. Santa Barbara's No. 1 singles player, Nathan Jackmon, was 
top seeded in the singles tournament but was upset by Temple City's Sandy 
Gentile, 0-6, 7-5, 6-1, in the semifinals Saturday. Santa Barbara's No. 1 
doubles team of Ian Carrera and Jimmy Walker won the boys' doubles championship 
at Ojai, but were upset by Jason Meyers and Robbie Wilkins of University, 6-2, 
6-2, Friday, in the quarterfinals of the Southern Section doubles tournament. 
In Division III, two familiar teams return to the final. Before last year, 
Pasadena Poly and Brentwood had met in the final in four consecutive years. 
Pasadena Poly defeated Brentwood for the title in 1989, '91 and '92; Brentwood 
beat Pasadena Poly for the championship in '90. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
