BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; DODGERS; WORRELL GETS A VOTE OF CONFIDENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Todd Worrell and Manager Tom Lasorda have met and discussed the closer 
situation, one that Worrell had concerns about after being taken out of 
Sunday's game in the ninth inning. Worrell said Lasorda told him he is still 
the closer. 
</P>
<P>
 "We talked about that and other things," Worrell said, "but everything is 
fine. I told Tommy that when I have pitched other places I'm used to staying 
out there until I got the job done or not. I haven't been taken out of games 
like that until I came here, and it's not something I'm used to dealing with. 
But Tommy told me that in that situation, he didn't think I had my stuff, and 
that's his prerogative. " 
</P>
<P>
 Worrell put the tying and winning runs on in the ninth inning with one out 
Sunday before Darren Dreifort relieved him and got the final two outs.  
</P>
<P>
 Since returning from the disabled list May 23, Worrell has struggled, blowing 
two saves in five appearances, but says his arm feels fine. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
