<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; WILLIAMS HOME ON RANGE WITH RELEASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As expected, the Houston Astros released reliever Mitch Williams Tuesday. In 
anticipation of the move, Williams, 29, had already left the team to return to 
his Texas ranch. 
</P>
<P>
 Officially, Williams was placed on waivers for the purpose of giving him his 
unconditional release. If he isn't claimed -- and no claims are expected -- he 
will be released Friday. The Astros are responsible for the rest of his 
$2.5-million salary this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, obtained in a trade with Philadelphia on Dec. 2, was 1-4 this season 
with a 7.65 earned-run average. He had six saves with two blown chances and 
gave up 21 hits and walked 24 batters in 20 innings. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 According to the June 6 edition of Sports Illustrated, Darryl Strawberry, 
released a week ago by the Dodgers, is bound to a divorce settlement with his 
ex-wife, Lisa, and their two children, Darryl Jr., 8, and Diamond Nicole, 5, 
worth $80,000 a month. . . . The Boston Red Sox acquired outfielder Wes 
Chamberlain and minor league pitcher Mike Sullivan from the Philadelphia 
Phillies in exchange for outfielder Billy Hatcher and pitcher Paul Quantrill. 
</P>
