<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; JOHNSTON PITCHES PARACLETE PAST CROSSROADS, 3-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jamie Johnston pitched a six-hitter, striking out six and walking three to 
lead Paraclete High to a 3-0 victory over Crossroads in a Southern Section 
Division V semifinal softball game Tuesday at Lancaster City Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The shutout was the 12th of the season for Johnston (18-5) and propelled the 
second-seeded Spirits into Saturday's championship game against Cerritos Valley 
Christian, a 3-0 winner over La Reina in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Paraclete (20-4-5) took a 1-0 lead in the first inning on Ariena Bass' double. 
Bass later scored on a fielding error. Jessica Jackson's single added a run in 
the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Crossroads, the defending Division V champion, finished the season with 21-7 
record. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos Valley Christian 3, La Reina 0 -- Jennifer Baltruzak pitched a 
four-hitter and struck out five, but La Reina (17-10) committed four errors in 
the Division V semifinal at the Cerritos Sports Complex. 
</P>
<P>
 The Regents were held to one hit -- Sara Heiler's one-out infield single in 
the sixth -- by Suzie Schoales, who struck out 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop Amat 3, Canyon 1 -- Chrissy Gil had two triples and pitched 4 1/3 
innings to lead Bishop Amat in the Southern Section Division II semifinals at 
Charter Oak High. 
</P>
<P>
 With two out in the top of the third inning, Gil (11-2) came on to pitch the 
rest of the way, allowing only one hit and striking out six. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon finished 19-6-1. 
</P>
