<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matt Olsen 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Royal 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Olsen suffered torn ligaments in his left ankle two days 
before the start of the season and was sidelined for more than two months. He 
returned to action six weeks ago and helped Royal win the Southern Section 
Division II championship in only his second season playing volleyball. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Olsen, a 6-foot-6 opposite hitter, was at his best when it 
counted most, contributing 38 kills in Saturday's championship victory against 
Highland. In the fourth and final game, Royal's Josh White set the ball to 
Olsen an astounding 35 times, and Olsen responded with 17 kills. "We told our 
setter if he set it to anyone else when he had a chance to set it to Olsen, 
we'd take him out," Royal Coach Bob Ferguson joked. In Wednesday's semifinal 
victory against South Torrance, Olsen had a match-high 17 kills. On Thursday, 
Olsen signed a letter of intent to play at Brigham Young. 
</P>
