MAN STUCK IN ROCKS IS FREED AFTER 10 HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who was trapped upside-down in a pile of boulders for 10 hours was 
rescued by firefighters who had to dig underneath the rocks with their hands. 
</P>
<P>
 Francis Queenan, 52, of Marlboro suffered cuts and bruises and was in fair 
condition Tuesday at University of Massachusetts Medical Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Queenan apparently was reaching into the pile behind a department 
store Monday and slid in about 6 1/2 feet, head-first and at a 45-degree angle. 
</P>
<P>
 He was stuck for about eight hours before anyone saw him and called rescuers. 
</P>
