<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 28 DRUNK-DRIVING ARRESTS REPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Highway Patrol arrested 28 suspected drunken drivers in Ventura 
County over the Memorial Day weekend, down from 40 arrests last year, officials 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, one person died in a drunk-driving accident, but there were no 
fatalities over this year's 78-hour maximum enforcement period that began at 6 
p.m. Friday and ended at midnight Monday, CHP Officer Staci Morse said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We had a good weekend," Morse said. "The awareness level is starting to 
elevate among people." 
</P>
<P>
 Morse said heightened media coverage and ongoing educational programs have 
caused more residents to avoid drinking and driving, and to use designated 
drivers. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
