<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; WALLET THIEVES TARGET GROCERY SHOPPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After noticing a surge of thefts at local grocery stores, Santa Paula police 
are warning shoppers against thieves who are taking wallets from shopping 
carts. 
</P>
<P>
 "I noticed that we had about a dozen in the last four to six months," police 
Sgt. Gary Marshall said. 
</P>
<P>
 Typically the thief waits for the victim to become distracted with shopping 
duties before taking the wallet, Marshall said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They're pretty slick. No one's ever seen anyone around their cart or 
anything," Marshall said. Police have no suspects in the thefts, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall advises carrying handbags on shoulders, and remembering to keep them 
zipped closed. He also advocates shopping with a friend or using fanny packs to 
make it more difficult for thieves. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think it's just part of an everyday awareness of your environment," 
Marshall said. "People need to be a little more alert and attentive to detail." 
PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
