<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; 2 FOOT RACES TO HELP TEEN RIDES PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDREW LePAGE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Runners and walkers can test their lungs along the trails of Laguna Niguel 
Regional Park on June 12 in two foot races that will raise money for a 
nonprofit group that provides safe rides home for intoxicated teens. 
</P>
<P>
 A five-kilometer run/stride and a 10-kilometer race will start at 7:30 and 
8:30 a.m., respectively, at the T.J. Maxx clothing store, 27271 La Paz Road, in 
the Plaza de la Paz Shopping Center in Laguna Niguel.The courses will wind 
through the park. 
</P>
<P>
 The $15 registration fee for the second annual "Maxximum 5K/10K Run" will 
benefit South County Safe Rides, a Boy Scouts Explorer program aimed at 
preventing teen-age drivers under the influence of alcohol or other drugs from 
driving. Safe rides home are provided between 10 p.m. and 2 a.m. on Friday and 
Saturday nights. 
</P>
<P>
 For more race information, call (714) 831-6163. ANDREW LePAGE 
</P>
</TEXT>
