<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nissan Motor Co. Returns to Profit: Japan's second-biggest car maker reported 
that it was back in the black for the fiscal year ended in March, but the 
company predicted that it will merely break even for fiscal 1995 as near-term 
business conditions remain tough.Nissan reported a current profit for its 
parent of $39.4 million for the year, contrasted with a loss of $252 million 
for the previous year. The company had a profit of $843 million for fiscal 
1992. Heiichi Hamaoka, an executive managing director for Nissan, attributed 
the turnaround to cost cutting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
