that the high court will not strike down curfews as broadly unconstitutional. 
However, some lower courts have invalidated curfews that do not permit 
exceptions for teen-agers who work or are accompanied by their parents. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other decisions also restrict First Amendment rights. 
</P>
<P>
