<P>
ISRAELIS KILL 2 PALESTINIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Israeli security forces shot and killed two fugitive Palestinians Tuesday as 
the two men got off a bus in a West Bank town near Jerusalem, bystanders said. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents of Al Ram took to the streets in protest, and soldiers fired tear 
gas to disperse the crowds. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said Israeli security forces posed as vegetable vendors in a van 
near a bus stop. When the bus stopped, the security forces asked two young 
Palestinians to step forward. Then, without warning, the troops started 
shooting, the witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 Army officials confirmed the shootings but declined comment on whether the 
Palestinians, both members of the radical Hamas group, were shot without 
warning. 
</P>
<P>
 Adel abu Sneneh, 34, said he saw five Israelis get out of the Ford and two 
shot at the Palestinians. He said that after the two Palestinians fell the 
Israelis kept shooting. Sneneh said a soldier put a gun next to one body and 
photographed it. 
