<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORMER USHER'S SUIT ACCUSES EMPLOYER OF RAPE; COURTS: YOUNG WOMAN ALLEGES THE 
THEATER MANAGER ASSAULTED HER, THEN FIRED HER WHEN SHE THREATENED TO TELL. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE TAMAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-age former theater usher has sued Cineplex Odeon Corp. and her 
ex-supervisor, alleging that he sexually harassed and raped her at the 
company's Universal City Cinemas, then fired her when she threatened to 
complain. 
</P>
<P>
 The young woman alleges in a lawsuit filed in Los Angeles Superior Court that 
George Webb, manager of the theaters, began telling her how "good her body was 
and how much he would like to see more of it" in October, 1992, just three 
weeks after she had been hired. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the lawsuit, the harassment escalated on Christmas Eve, 1992, 
after Webb summoned the woman and another employee into his office and showed 
them a gun. The suit alleges that he then called the woman alone to his office 
and began hugging and kissing her and later that same evening told her that 
wanted to "see her body." 
</P>
<P>
 At that point, the young woman tried to flee Webb's office, but he grabbed her 
and held her hands behind her body, ripped off her clothes and then brandished 
the gun he had shown her earlier, according to the lawsuit. Webb subsequently 
held her down and performed several sex acts on her, the suit alleges. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the lawsuit, on another occasion Webb grabbed the girl by her 
hair and raped her. 
</P>
<P>
 Webb said he would fire her if she told anyone, and did fire her last May when 
she threatened to complain after being repeatedly harassed, the suit contends. 
The suit did not say to whom she threatened to complain.  
</P>
<P>
 Webb could not be reached for comment Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 An unidentified detective at the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department said 
there is no record that the young woman who brought the lawsuit ever filed a 
criminal complaint against Webb with either the Sheriff's Department or the Los 
Angeles Police Department. Stephan Math, an attorney representing the young 
woman, declined to discuss the case. 
</P>
<P>
 Cineplex spokesman Howard Lichtman said his company has fired Webb and is 
discussing a possible settlement with the young woman's attorney. 
</P>
<P>
 The young woman is seeking an unspecified amount of general and punitive 
damages in her lawsuit, which alleges intentional infliction of emotional 
distress and violation of state sexual discrimination laws. 
</P>
<P>
 Cineplex Odeon has a detailed policy in place allowing employees to report 
sexual harassment to the company's highest officials, Lichtman said. 
</P>
<P>
 In her lawsuit, the young woman alleges that Cineplex had received other 
complaints of the same nature regarding Webb but chose to ignore them. Lichtman 
said his company is unaware of any other such complaints about Webb. 
</P>
</TEXT>
