SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; $50,000 IN JEWELRY TAKEN IN HOLDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nine people were held at gunpoint Tuesday afternoon during the robbery of 
about $50,000 worth of merchandise from a jewelry store, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the holdup, which took place just after noon at 
aPalmdale Jewelry Mart, 2728 E. Palmdale Blvd., said Los Angeles Sheriff's Sgt. 
Bob Denham. 
</P>
<P>
 Denham said a man, armed with a semiautomatic pistol, and his female partner, 
both in their 20s, entered the store and threatened employees and customers 
while gathering up the jewelry. 
</P>
<P>
 "We know it was a substantial amount -- over $50,000 worth," Denham said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two robbers fled from the store in an unknown direction. No getaway car 
was seen, Denham said. 
