<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE; BIG-NAME BUILDERS SHOW INTEREST IN NEWEST IRVINE 
COMMUNITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At least 12 big-name home builders -- including the Presley Cos., Costain 
Homes and Kaufman & Broad -- are reportedly bidding to buy a portion of 100 
acres that make up the first phase of Northwood Point, the Irvine Co.'s newest 
planned community in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 There will be about 700 single-family detached homes in the first phase of 
Northwood, which will be north of Interstate 5 at Culver Drive just north of 
Irvine Boulevard, an Irvine Co. spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a very favorable location, especially with the opening of the Foothill 
corridor toll road. This will continue to push real estate values upward in all 
the areas that it serves," said Robert McFarland, senior vice president with 
Market Profiles, a real estate consulting firm in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine Co. is reviewing the offers and is expected to announce the winning 
bidders this week. 
</P>
