<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mediation Service Created: Several business people have created a new 
mediation service that will specialize in solving real estate disputes, such as 
shoddy construction or contract disputes.The founders say they are poised to 
capitalize on a state bill that, if passed, would require a certain portion of 
real estate disputes to be solved by arbitration rather than by costly 
lawsuits.  
</P>
<P>
 The founders are: James T. Capretz, a Newport Beach attorney, William Cote, a 
luxury real estate broker in Newport Beach and Joseph Di Mento, a former 
assistant vice chancellor at UC Irvine. They have formed Real Estate 
Arbitration & Mediation Services in Newport Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
