<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SensorMedics: The maker of products for respiratory care has filed a lawsuit 
claiming that a competitor is infringing on its patent for a "breath-by-breath" 
analysis process. 
</P>
<P>
 The lawsuit, which was filed Friday in federal court in Minnesota, responds to 
an earlier claim by Medical Graphics Corp. that it holds a patent it says 
SensorMedics is infringing. Yorba Linda-based SensorMedics has also alleged 
that Medical Graphics Corp. of St. Paul, Minn., is participating in deceptive 
trade practices and unfair competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
