<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: 4 ACCUSED OF TURNING BACK USED-CAR ODOMETERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four Orange County men have been charged with criminal conspiracy and grand 
theft for allegedly participating in a scheme to set back odometers on used 
cars, the district attorney's office said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Twelve charges were filed by the district attorney's office based on an 
investigation by the Department of Motor Vehicles at Europe Auto Sales. Those 
charged are Phuoc Hong Pham, 28; Tuyet Kim Le, 43, and Minh Lac Au, 49, all of 
Westminster, and Dung Kim Le, 52, of Midway City. 
</P>
<P>
 The DMV has also initiated action to revoke the dealership's license. The 
agency's investigator alleges that 12 cars were sold with reset odometers, with 
a loss to victims of $75,110. 
</P>
</TEXT>
