<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHERE ARE THEY NOW?; BILLY COWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times staff writer David W. Myers catches up with former Dodgers and Angels. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Yankees sold Cowan to the Angels at the end of a trip to Anaheim in the 
summer of 1969.He responded with a home run in his first pinch-hit appearance a 
few days later and batted .304 for the rest of the season. An outfielder, Cowan 
was making a rare start at first base when the Angels completed the first 
triple play in team history on June 26, 1970. 
</P>
<P>
 Cowan, 55, began selling real estate after the Angels released him in 1972. He 
lives in Palos Verdes Estates. 
