<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BETTER SHOT AT STATE GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All three Orange County theater troupes seeking state funding have been given 
stronger grant recommendations this year than last by a California Arts Council 
advisory panel. 
</P>
<P>
 The panel, which met last week in Sacramento, upped the rankings used to 
determine grant amounts: Costa Mesa's South Coast Repertory went from 4-minus 
to 4 (the top score on a 1-to-4 scale); and Laguna Playhouse and Fullerton 
Civic Light Opera both went from 3-minus to 3. 
</P>
<P>
 The higher ranks do not necessarily mean larger grants, because the CAC's 
overall budget has not yet been determined. Last year SCR was awarded $57,765, 
Fullerton Civic Light Opera received $4,705, and Laguna Playhouse was awarded 
$5,984. 
</P>
<P>
 The panel also gave the Santa Ana-based Orange County Crazies comedy group, in 
its first try for a CAC grant, a 2-minus. Typically, the CAC gives funds only 
to groups ranked 3 or above. ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
